{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-03","name":"John Cranmer","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"John Cranmer","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"John"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Cranmer"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1425–Male","fullLifespan":"about 1425–","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-72372-475-96/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/36480628","headline":"CRANMER FAMILY HISTORY FOLLOWS:","description":"MAY 5, 2017\n\nTHOMAS CRANMER, ARCHBISHOP OF CANTERBURY, was born 2 July 1489, at Aslacton, Watton Parish, Nottinghamshire, England, to Thomas Cranmer Esq (1468-1501) and Agnes Hatfield (1470-1556.)  He …","@type":"MediaObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-72372-475-96/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/36480628","headline":"CRANMER FAMILY HISTORY FOLLOWS:","description":"MAY 5, 2017\n\nTHOMAS CRANMER, ARCHBISHOP OF CANTERBURY, was born 2 July 1489, at Aslacton, Watton Parish, Nottinghamshire, England, to Thomas Cranmer Esq (1468-1501) and Agnes Hatfield (1470-1556.)  He …","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthDate":"+1425","birthPlace":{"address":"Aslacton, Watton Parish, England","geo":{"latitude":52.46692,"longitude":1.17151,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nJohn Cranmer was the heir of Edmund Cranmer and his wife Isabella de Aslacton, the daughter and heiress of William de Aslacton, \"of knight's degree\", by which marriage the inheritance of Aslacton passed into the Cranmer line. Edmund Cranmer apparently sold his own holdings in Sutterton, Lincolnshire on the marriage, which must have taken place before 1425/6, when they claimed additional land in Aslacton from William Sibthorpe, Esq. Accordingly, John Cranmer's birth should be dated about 1425.\n\nJohn Cranmer married a daughter of the Marshall family of South Carleton in North Muskham; most sources call her Alice. The marriage was probably about 1450, with two sons born afterward: Thomas, the eldest and heir, and John, a priest.\n\nThere is apparently no record available of John Cranmer's death.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1425","date":"about 1425","place":"Aslacton, Watton Parish, England"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1455","date":"about 1455","place":"Aslockton, Nottinghamshire, England","age":"30","id":"LZ2Z-7WB"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1457","date":"abt 1457","place":"of Aslacton, Nttnghm, Engl","age":"32","id":"MYPZ-W9L"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0"}],"parent":[{"name":"Edmund Cranmer of Sutterton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1400–Male","birthDate":"A+1400","@type":"Person","identifier":"GK5Y-RT8","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GK5Y-RT8/edmund-cranmer-of-sutterton-1400","published":true},{"name":"Isabella Aslacton","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1405–Female","birthDate":"+1405/","@type":"Person","identifier":"GK5Y-55Q","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GK5Y-55Q/isabella-aslacton-1405","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"John Cranmer","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1425–Male","birthDate":"A+1425","@type":"Person","identifier":"GK5B-QVM","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GK5B-QVM/john-cranmer-1425","published":true}],"spouse":[{"name":"Alice Marshall","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1430–Female","birthDate":"A+1430","@type":"Person","identifier":"MYPZ-4MG","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/MYPZ-4MG/alice-marshall-1430","published":true}],"children":[{"name":"Thomas Cranmer","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1455–1501","birthDate":"A+1455","deathDate":"+1501-05-27","age":46,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/wrbpj/thu